From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: pg_duckdb downstream
Date: Thu, 24 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] common: drop redundant out-of-line constexpr defs for
 FileFlags members

src/common/file_system.cpp carries 14 out-of-line constexpr redeclarations
of FileFlags::FILE_FLAGS_* -- vestigial C++14 idiom. In DuckDB's C++17
build these are no-ops at the language level (the in-class static
constexpr declarations are already implicitly inline), but GCC in Debug
(-O0) still emits them as storage-backed symbols in libduckdb_static.a.

The vortex extension's own C++ code (vortex-duckdb/cpp/file_system.cpp)
odr-uses FILE_FLAGS_READ / FILE_FLAGS_PARALLEL_ACCESS when compiling
against v1.5.2 headers, which pushes the same symbols into
libvortex_duckdb.a. Linking the loadable vortex.duckdb_extension then
fails with "multiple definition of duckdb::FileFlags::FILE_FLAGS_READ"
on every Debug build.

Dropping the redundant out-of-line defs lets the C++17 implicit-inline
rule kick in, the remaining copies become COMDAT-merged, and the
collision goes away. Release/ReleaseStatic builds are unaffected
because at -O2 these constants are already inlined into their use sites.
---
diff --git a/src/common/file_system.cpp b/src/common/file_system.cpp
index 8b83c25c60..ae687a8b45 100644
--- a/src/common/file_system.cpp
+++ b/src/common/file_system.cpp
@@ -48,20 +48,6 @@ extern "C" WINBASEAPI BOOL WINAPI GetPhysicallyInstalledSystemMemory(PULONGLONG)
 
 namespace duckdb {
 
-constexpr FileOpenFlags FileFlags::FILE_FLAGS_READ;
-constexpr FileOpenFlags FileFlags::FILE_FLAGS_WRITE;
-constexpr FileOpenFlags FileFlags::FILE_FLAGS_DIRECT_IO;
-constexpr FileOpenFlags FileFlags::FILE_FLAGS_FILE_CREATE;
-constexpr FileOpenFlags FileFlags::FILE_FLAGS_FILE_CREATE_NEW;
-constexpr FileOpenFlags FileFlags::FILE_FLAGS_APPEND;
-constexpr FileOpenFlags FileFlags::FILE_FLAGS_PRIVATE;
-constexpr FileOpenFlags FileFlags::FILE_FLAGS_NULL_IF_NOT_EXISTS;
-constexpr FileOpenFlags FileFlags::FILE_FLAGS_PARALLEL_ACCESS;
-constexpr FileOpenFlags FileFlags::FILE_FLAGS_EXCLUSIVE_CREATE;
-constexpr FileOpenFlags FileFlags::FILE_FLAGS_NULL_IF_EXISTS;
-constexpr FileOpenFlags FileFlags::FILE_FLAGS_MULTI_CLIENT_ACCESS;
-constexpr FileOpenFlags FileFlags::FILE_FLAGS_DISABLE_LOGGING;
-constexpr FileOpenFlags FileFlags::FILE_FLAGS_ENABLE_EXTENSION_INSTALL;
 
 void FileOpenFlags::Verify() {
 #ifdef DEBUG
